snippet.textDisplay:
I've only ever bought 2 games from EA 
NFS Rivals 2 years after release
Anthem 1 month after release 
I didn't pre-order any game besides horizon zero dawn on steam for 8$. 
Why did I buy anthem? 
Trailer blew me away 
I enjoyed the Open beta, 
Yes I enjoyed it, played for 6hrs in 48hr open beta. 
Enjoyed the combat and flight in the game (there's literally no other game like it on pc). 

After purchase
Yeah the story was shitty 
Yeah loot grind was shitty. 
Dropped the game 
It's been 19 months since I last played it. 
Was really hoping it to get fixed cause combat and movement just felt too good. 

2 years after game release, 23 months since I bought it. 

Anthem is dead
My hopes have been killed. 
Why? üò≠üò≠üò≠
Pc gaming sucks 
Moving to ps5 for single player exclusives 
Never gonna play multiplayer 
I'm done with these so called AAA game publishers

If it's online focused screw it. 

Seeing as I haven't bought more than 2 games and I won't be buying any way game until it has good reviews 5 months after release. 

Now tell me am I an idiot?
